cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and entity disambiguation. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as entity disambiguation is a common task in information retrieval. Additionally, the use of machine learning models for entity disambiguation suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of embeddings and the development of a novel approach for learning entity representations suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
